6 TEEN-AGE GIRLS

04:02.329 --> 04:03.547
MARCHING THROUGH
THE MAIN GATE,

04:03.547 --> 04:05.245
YOU THINK SOMEONE
WOULD NOTICE?

04:05.245 --> 04:06.985
UNLESS YOU SNUCK
BETWEEN BUNKER HALL

04:06.985 --> 04:08.813
AND THE KEYSER
ATHLETIC BUILDING,

04:08.813 --> 04:11.033
WHICH SORT OF LETS YOU OUT
AT THE BUS STOP ON DILBY STREET.

04:11.033 --> 04:13.122
SO IF YOU WENT
THROUGH THE WINDOW
IN THE BATHROOM,

04:13.122 --> 04:15.690
YOU'D ONLY HAVE A
ONE-STORY DROP TO THE
ROOF OF THE COMMON ROOM,

04:15.690 --> 04:17.039
AND THEN YOU COULD
CROSS BEHIND THE QUAD,

04:17.039 --> 04:19.171
WHICH HAS, LIKE,
NO LIGHTS TO SPEAK OF.

04:20.738 --> 04:21.739
OR NOT.

04:25.743 --> 04:28.093
DON'T I HAVE
A SAY IN THIS?

04:28.093 --> 04:30.357
SWEETHEART, IT'S PART
OF THE SETTLEMENT.

04:30.357 --> 04:32.750
WE DON'T HAVE A CHOICE.

04:32.750 --> 04:36.101
NEITHER YOUR FATHER OR I
CAN AFFORD TO BUY
EACH OTHER OUT,

04:36.101 --> 04:37.581
AND THE TRUTH IS,

04:37.581 --> 04:40.715
NEITHER ONE OF US NEEDS
A PLACE THIS BIG ANYWAY.

04:40.715 --> 04:43.065
HONEY, WE HAVE TO
BE PRACTICAL.

04:43.065 --> 04:45.415
RIGHT. PRACTICAL.

04:45.415 --> 04:50.072
ALL YOU NEED TO TELL US
IS WHAT YOU WANT US TO
DO WITH YOUR STUFF.

04:50.072 --> 04:54.598
DO YOU WANT YOUR FATHER
AND I TO DIVIDE IT
BETWEEN US,

04:54.598 --> 04:59.124
OR IF YOU LIKE,
I CAN MOVE IT ALL
EXACTLY AS IT IS HERE

04:59.124 --> 05:01.518
TO WHEREVER I GO.

05:01.518 --> 05:03.433
THAT'S NOT THE SAME.

05:03.433 --> 05:05.957
IT'S JUST
GLORIFIED STORAGE.

05:07.916 --> 05:12.094
SARAH, HONEY...

05:12.094 --> 05:15.315
WHAT DO YOU
WANT ME TO DO?

05:17.534 --> 05:19.623
WELL...

05:19.623 --> 05:24.889
I WAS KIND OF GOING FOR
A SLEEK, CONTEMPORARY
VIBE IN HERE,

05:24.889 --> 05:28.197
BUT IF YOU WERE THINKING
MORE ALONG THE LINES OF
ROMPER ROOM...

05:28.197 --> 05:31.287
OH...I COULDN'T JUST
STICK IT IN THE GUEST ROOM

05:31.287 --> 05:33.681
IN MY MOM'S NEW APARTMENT
OR MY DAD'S NEW PLACE

05:33.681 --> 05:35.857
AND THEN PRETEND
I GREW UP THERE.

05:35.857 --> 05:39.774
IT'S LIKE, WHEREVER
THEY END UP, IT'S NOT
GONNA BE MY HOME, RIGHT?

05:39.774 --> 05:41.253
HEY...

05:41.253 --> 05:42.820
HEY, IT'S OK.

05:42.820 --> 05:44.822
THERE'S PLENTY OF ROOM
FOR EVERYTHING HERE.

05:47.259 --> 05:49.479
YOU KNOW WHAT?

05:49.479 --> 05:54.136
I REALLY SEE THIS WORKING
IN THE BATHROOM.

05:54.136 --> 05:57.748
IT'S NEVER
GOING TO BE
LIKE IT WAS, IS IT?

06:01.230 --> 06:03.101
NO.

06:03.101 --> 06:05.452
IT'S LIKE DOMINOES.

06:05.452 --> 06:07.584
PARENTS SPLIT,

06:07.584 --> 06:08.933
APARTMENT GETS SOLD,

06:08.933 --> 06:10.413
FAMILY DISAPPEARS.

06:10.413 --> 06:13.460
CLICK, CLICK, CLICK.

06:13.460 --> 06:16.332
I JUST KEEP THINKING
ABOUT MY MOM.

06:16.332 --> 06:18.116
YEAH.

06:18.116 --> 06:19.944
IT'S GONNA BE
A BIG CHANGE FOR HER.

06:19.944 --> 06:21.859
HOW OLD WAS SHE WHEN
SHE MARRIED YOUR DAD?

06:21.859 --> 06:24.993
NO. MY MOM.
MY REAL MOM.
MY BIRTH MOTHER.

06:24.993 --> 06:26.473
ROBIN?

06:26.473 --> 06:28.213
YEAH.

06:28.213 --> 06:30.520
YEAH. YOU KNOW, WHEN I
MET HER A COUPLE YEARS AGO,

06:30.520 --> 06:33.001
SHE WAS
JUST THIS PERSON,

06:33.001 --> 06:36.047
THIS REALLY COOL PERSON
WHO WAS KIND OF LIVING
HER OWN LIFE

06:36.047 --> 06:38.789
AND WALKING AROUND
WITH THE SAME DNA AS ME.

06:38.789 --> 06:41.009
BUT I DIDN'T NEED HER
TO BE MORE THAN THAT,

06:41.009 --> 06:44.447
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW,
I HAD A FAMILY.

06:44.447 --> 06:45.492
BUT NOW...

06:49.800 --> 06:53.021
COME ON, NOW. EVERYONE'S
GOT TO SHARE HERE.

06:53.021 --> 06:54.588
DEREK.

06:54.588 --> 06:58.069
THE THING
I DIDN'T EXPECT, HUH?

06:58.069 --> 07:00.071
OK. HONESTLY,
I DIDN'T EXPECT

07:00.071 --> 07:03.248
TO FIND CHERYL SO SEXY
IN HER THIRD TRIMESTER.

07:03.248 --> 07:04.989
WELL, IT'S TRUE.

07:04.989 --> 07:07.514
WE ARE KINDA HAVING SEX
ALL THE TIME.

07:07.514 --> 07:09.516
I DIDN'T EXPECT THAT.

07:09.516 --> 07:12.736
I SEE JILL AND HENRY
NODDING BACK THERE.

07:12.736 --> 07:13.824
ANYONE ELSE?

07:13.824 --> 07:15.260
[SOBBING]

07:15.260 --> 07:18.089
I DIDN'T EXPECT TO
LOVE THE BABY SO MUCH.

07:18.089 --> 07:20.178
I MEAN, HE'S
NOT EVEN HERE YET,

07:20.178 --> 07:23.051
BUT I CAN'T EVEN
EXPLAIN IT IN WORDS.

07:23.051 --> 07:26.228
I JUST LOVE HIM
SO MUCH.

07:26.228 --> 07:28.883
IT'S OVERWHELMING,
ISN'T IT?

07:28.883 --> 07:33.670
LADIES, DON'T LET
ANYONE TELL YOU THAT'S
JUST HORMONES TALKING.

07:33.670 --> 07:39.415
THERE'S A VERY REAL
BOND DEVELOPING BETWEEN
YOU AND YOUR CHILD.

07:39.415 --> 07:42.679
HE FEELS YOUR LAUGHTER,
HE KNOWS YOUR
MOVEMENTS...

07:42.679 --> 07:44.855
OK, WHO DOES THAT LEAVE?

07:44.855 --> 07:48.380
LET'S--DAPHNE, CHARLIE,
WHAT WOULD YOU SAY

07:48.380 --> 07:49.730
HAS BEEN
THE BIGGEST SURPRISE?

07:52.515 --> 07:54.474
UH...
UH...

07:54.474 --> 07:56.693
WELL, I--LET'S SEE.
UM...

07:56.693 --> 07:59.914
